<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>


  <!-- Crude Implants -->

  <HediffDef Name="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase" Abstract="True">
    <hediffClass>Hediff_Implant</hediffClass>
    <defaultLabelColor>(.78, 0.36, 0.36)</defaultLabelColor>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_SuturedMouth</defName>
    <label>sutured mouth</label>
    <labelNoun>a sutured mouth</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This person's mouth has been sutured shut with cloth.  They cannot talk and can barely eat.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<painOffset>.03</painOffset>
		<capMods>
          <li>
            <capacity>Talking</capacity>
            <setMax>0.0</setMax>
          </li>
          <li>
            <capacity>Eating</capacity>
            <setMax>0.1</setMax>
          </li>
        </capMods>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<spawnThingOnRemoved>Cloth</spawnThingOnRemoved>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_SuturedEye</defName>
    <label>sutured eye</label>
    <labelNoun>a sutured eye</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This person's eye has been sutured shut, making them unable to see through the eye.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<painOffset>.02</painOffset>
		<partEfficiencyOffset>-1</partEfficiencyOffset>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<spawnThingOnRemoved>Cloth</spawnThingOnRemoved>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_SteelSpikes</defName>
	<label>implanted steel spikes</label>
    <labelNoun>a set of steel spikes</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This person has had steel spikes embedded into various parts of their bodies.  Very painful, but actually can be used as a weapon too.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<painOffset>.15</painOffset>
		<partEfficiencyOffset>-.1</partEfficiencyOffset>
		<vomitMtbDays>5</vomitMtbDays>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_VerbGiver">
        <tools>
          <li>
            <label>steel spike</label>
            <capacities>
              <li>Stab</li>
            </capacities>
            <power>10.0</power>
            <cooldownTime>3</cooldownTime>
            <alwaysTreatAsWeapon>true</alwaysTreatAsWeapon>
          </li>
        </tools>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <!-- ================================== Organ Implants =====================================-->
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_HeartIrregulator</defName>
    <label>heart irregulator</label>
    <labelNoun>a heart irregulator</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant causes regular heart palpitations.  These will cause periodic chestpains every few days.  Unfortunately, these turn into heart attacks eventually.   Someone with one of these installed will suffer a heart attack if hit with an EMP charge.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<partEfficiencyOffset>-.25</partEfficiencyOffset>
		<hediffGivers>
            <li Class="HediffGiver_Random">
              <hediff>WCE2_Chestpains</hediff>
              <mtbDays>2</mtbDays>
              <partsToAffect>
                <li>Heart</li>
              </partsToAffect>
            </li>
          </hediffGivers>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>HeartAttack</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_SleepDeprivator</defName>
    <label>sleep deprivator</label>
    <labelNoun>a sleep deprivator</labelNoun>
	<description>This torturous implant ensures the patient has a difficult time sleeping, keeping them in a constant, torturous state of insomnia.  EMP damage causes immediate lethargy.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<restFallFactor>1.5</restFallFactor>
		<statOffsets>
			<RestRateMultiplier>-0.75</RestRateMultiplier>
		</statOffsets>
		<hediffGivers>
            <li Class="HediffGiver_Random">
              <hediff>WCE2_Lethargic</hediff>
              <mtbDays>5</mtbDays>
              <partsToAffect>
                <li>Brain</li>
              </partsToAffect>
            </li>
          </hediffGivers>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_Lethargic</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_PainAmplifier</defName>
    <label>pain amplifier</label>
    <labelNoun>a pain amplifier</labelNoun>
	<description>This torturous implant increases both the pain shock threshold of a person and amplifies the amount of pain they feel.  Masochists love it, but everyone else dreads it.  EMP Damage causes immediate, searing pain in every nerve.</description>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<painFactor>1.25</painFactor>
		<statOffsets>
          <PainShockThreshold>0.20</PainShockThreshold>
        </statOffsets>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_SearingPain</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_AggressionAmplifier</defName>
    <label>aggression amplifier</label>
    <labelNoun>an aggression amplifier</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant causes greatly hightened aggression, causing social fights but also greatly improving the patient's melee combat skills.  Also causes constant tantrums and occasional fits of murderous or sadistic rage.  Eventually will cause the person to go berserk until subdued.  EMP damage causes instant berserking.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<socialFightChanceFactor>10.0</socialFightChanceFactor>
		<statOffsets>
          <MeleeHitChance>10</MeleeHitChance>
        </statOffsets>
		<mentalStateGivers>
          <li>
            <mentalState>Berserk</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>120</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>MurderousRage</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>60</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>SadisticRage</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>30</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>Tantrum</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>5</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>TargetedTantrum</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>5</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>BedroomTantrum</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>5</mtbDays>
          </li>
        </mentalStateGivers>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_BlindingRage</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_PanicInducer</defName>
    <label>panic inducer</label>
    <labelNoun>a panic inducer</labelNoun>
	<description>This torturous implant causes increased mental break threshold and periodic sad or psychotic wandering, eventually leading to giving up on their current settlement entirely if not 'gently' persuaded to stay with beatings.  EMP damage all but guarantees a psychotic break.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<statOffsets>
			<MentalBreakThreshold>0.20</MentalBreakThreshold>
		</statOffsets>
		<mentalStateGivers>
          <li>
            <mentalState>Wander_Psychotic</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>15</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>Wander_Sad</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>10</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>Wander_OwnRoom</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>5</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>GiveUpExit</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>120</mtbDays>
          </li>
        </mentalStateGivers>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_PanicAttack</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_StomachClamp</defName>
    <label>stomach clamp</label>
    <labelNoun>a stomach clamp</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<makesSickThought>true</makesSickThought>
	<description>This torturous implant periodically clamps, squeezes, and rumbles the stomach, causing regular vomiting and, despite the constant upset stomach, makes them hungry more.  EMP damage causes instant vomiting.</description>
    <stages>
      <li>
		<partEfficiencyOffset>-.2</partEfficiencyOffset>
		<painOffset>.07</painOffset>
		<vomitMtbDays>0.5</vomitMtbDays>
		<hungerRateFactor>0.25</hungerRateFactor>
		<statOffsets>
		  <EatingSpeed>-0.25</EatingSpeed>
        </statOffsets>
      </li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <vomit>true</vomit>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_HealingInhibitor</defName>
    <label>healing inhibitor</label>
    <labelNoun>a healing inhibitor</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant doesn't actually cause any pain or suffering, but greatly reduces their ability to heal from illness and injury and makes them more vulnerable to toxic materials.</description>
    <stages>
		<li>
			<naturalHealingFactor>0.75</naturalHealingFactor>
			<statOffsets>
				<ImmunityGainSpeed>-0.10</ImmunityGainSpeed>
				<ToxicResistance>-0.15</ToxicResistance>
			</statOffsets>
		</li>
    </stages>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_CoagulantSuppressor</defName>
    <label>coagulant suppressor</label>
    <labelNoun>a coagulant suppressor</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant makes it more difficult for their blood to coagulate.  They bleed easier and even minor cuts can be deadly.</description>
    <stages>
		<li>
			<totalBleedFactor>1.5</totalBleedFactor>
		</li>
    </stages>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_EmotionDestabilizer</defName>
    <label>emotion destabilizer</label>
    <labelNoun>an emotion destabilizer</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant makes the patient unable to keep control fo their emotions, causing great swings in opinions of others based on events and greatly increasing the chances of social fights.  They will periodically start going on insulting sprees, afterwhich they will apologize and probably cry a lot.</description>
    <stages>
		<li>
			<opinionOfOthersFactor>5.0</opinionOfOthersFactor>
			<socialFightChanceFactor>5.0</socialFightChanceFactor>
		<mentalStateGivers>
          <li>
            <mentalState>TargetedInsultingSpree</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>30</mtbDays>
          </li>
		  <li>
            <mentalState>InsultingSpree</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>15</mtbDays>
          </li>
        </mentalStateGivers>
		</li>
    </stages>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_MemoryExpulsor</defName>
    <label>memory expulsor</label>
    <labelNoun>a memory expulsor</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant causes frequent forgetfulness and reduces learning capacity.  Patients will periodically wander confused and will lose skills faster.  EMP Damage causes immediate and massive memory loss.</description>
    <stages>
		<li>
		<forgetMemoryThoughtMtbDays>1</forgetMemoryThoughtMtbDays>
		<statOffsets>
			<GlobalLearningFactor>-0.25</GlobalLearningFactor>
		</statOffsets>
		<mentalStateGivers>
          <li>
            <mentalState>WanderConfused</mentalState>
            <mtbDays>5</mtbDays>
          </li>
        </mentalStateGivers>
		</li>
    </stages>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_SkillDecay">
        <decayPerDayPercentageLevelCurve>
          <points>
            <li>(4, 0.05)</li>
            <li>(12, 0.15)</li>
            <li>(20, 0.25)</li>
          </points>
        </decayPerDayPercentageLevelCurve>
    </li>
	<li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_MemoryLoss</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_EMPRelay</defName>
    <label>EMP relay</label>
    <labelNoun>an EMP relay</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous implant doesn't do anything.  Unless they're hit by EMP, at which point it puts them into shock, allowing easy rescue - or capture.  Great for prisoners and troublesome pawns who you need to subdue constantly! Warning: repeated shocking of the brain may cause brain damage.</description>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_BrainShock</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  
  <HediffDef ParentName="WCE2_ImplantHediffBase">
    <defName>WCE2_EMPKillswitch</defName>
    <label>EMP Killswitch</label>
    <labelNoun>an EMP killswitch</labelNoun>
	<isBad>false</isBad>
	<description>This torturous device does nothing until hit by EMP, at which point it fries their brain like a slab of bacon.  Very rarely do pawns survive it, but there have been cases of survivors with severe, permanent, and crippling brain damage.  Cannibals get a craving for Cianti and fava beans when one of these goes off.</description>
	<comps>
      <li Class="HediffCompProperties_ReactOnDamage">
        <damageDefIncoming>EMP</damageDefIncoming>
        <createHediff>WCE2_EMPKillswitchOn</createHediff>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </HediffDef>
  

</Defs>
